  "url": "https://www.lankadeepa.lk/latest_news/\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba-\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca-\u0db1\u0dc0-\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2-\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca-\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dad\u0dca-\u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2/1-616417",
  "time_ut": 1657796987,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Appointing a new President is also too late due to the delay in the letter",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Since President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa did not hand in his resignation letter by the due date, the appointment of the new president by Parliament will also be delayed further.",
        "President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa was supposed to hand over his resignation letter to the Speaker yesterday (13), but it did not happen that day.",
        "If it was delivered on that day, the Parliament had previously decided to meet today (15) and start the process of calling for nominations to appoint the new President.",
        "But due to the delay in handing over the letter of resignation by the President, Parliament will not be able to meet today to appoint the new President.",
        "The Special Arrangements Act for Electing the President No. 2 of 1981 states that when a vacancy occurs in the office of the President when the Parliament has not been dissolved, it should be considered and implemented as if the Parliament had been convened within three days of the vacancy occurring.",
        "After that, the date and time fixed for that parliamentary meeting should be informed to the parliamentarians by the general secretary of the parliament.",
        "When the Parliament convenes in this way, the Secretary General should first inform the Parliament that there is a vacancy in the office of the President.",
        "A date and time on which nominations will be accepted on a date not earlier than 48 hours and not later than 7 days from the date of the meeting should also be announced there.",
        "It is mentioned in the bill that the parliament should meet on the day fixed for accepting the nominations and the general secretary of the parliament should act as the election officer."
      ],
